20identity%20among%20his%20peers%20was%20that%20he%20was%20the%20son-in-law%20of%20Infosys%20founder%20Narayana%20Murthy%2C%20whose%20businesswoman%20daughter%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fuk-pm-rishi-sunak-wife-akshata-murty-richer-than-king-charles-new-list-shows-5696606%5C%22%3EAkshata%20Murthy%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20married%20to%20him.%20Of%20course%2C%20he%20was%20blessed%20with%20degrees%20from%20prestigious%20institutions%2C%20such%20as%20Oxford%2C%20Stanford%20and%20Winchester%20College%2C%20but%20he%20had%20no%20political%20background.%20He%20was%20born%20in%201980%20in%20Southampton%20to%20working%20parents%20-%20his%20father%20was%20a%20doctor%20and%20mother%20a%20chemist.%20Both%20were%20Indian-origin%20and%20came%20from%20East%20Africa.%20Sunak%20himself%20was%20a%20proud%20and%20practising%20Hindu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20such%20a%20background%20hardly%20guarantees%20success%20in%20an%20election.%20So%2C%20did%20the%20Conservative%20Party%20gamble%20on%20an%20unknown%2034-year-old%20with%20a%20%26quot%3Bcollege%20kid%26quot%3B%20look%2C%20who%20until%20a%20year%20earlier%20had%20a%20flourishing%20career%20in%20investment%20banking%20in%20the%20US%3F%20Not%20at%20all%2C%20because%20the%20party%20had%20assigned%20Sunak%20its%20safest%20seat%20in%20the%20country.%20The%20party%20bosses%20must%20have%20seen%20something%20in%20him%20that%20prompted%20them%20to%20parachute%20him%20into%20a%20safe%20Tory%20haven.%20The%20initial%20reaction%20of%20Tory%20voters%20was%20that%20he%20%26quot%3Bwas%20not%20a%20local%20lad%26quot%3B.%20But%20Sunak%20won%20by%20a%20thumping%20majority.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUnderstanding%20Richmond%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERichmond%20is%20in%20the%20north%20of%20England%20in%20Yorkshire%2C%20a%20region%20known%20for%20its%20lack%20of%20wealth%20but%20not%20lack%20of%20beauty.%20However%2C%20made%20up%20of%20pretty%20rural%20villages%20and%20scenic%20semi-urban%20places%2C%20it%20is%20an%20island%20of%20prosperity.%20If%20Yorkshire%20is%20Labour%2C%20Richmond%20is%20defiantly%20Tory%20in%20Labour%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERichmond%20is%20such%20a%20safe%20Tory%20seat%20that%20Rishi%20Sunak%20did%20not%20have%20to%20work%20very%20hard%20to%20retain%20it%20in%20the%202017%20midterm%20polls%20and%20the%202019%20general%20elections.%20In%202022%2C%20just%20seven%20years%20after%20his%20first%20victory%2C%20he%20became%20the%20pride%20of%20his%20constituency%20by%20becoming%20the%20country's%20first%20non-White%20Prime%20Minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FRishi%2520Sunak%2C%2520UK%2527s%2520Accidental%2520Prime%2520Minister%2C%2520Goes%2520For%2520Broke%5C%22%3ERead%20%7C%C2%A0Rishi%20Sunak%2C%20UK's%20Accidental%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20Goes%20For%20Broke%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERishi%20Sunak%20is%20once%20again%20contesting%20from%20the%20safest%20Tory%20seat%20in%20the%20UK.%20The%20constituency%20has%20returned%20a%20Conservative%20MP%20since%201910%20and%20has%20sent%20some%20very%20high-profile%20politicians%20to%20Parliament.%20William%20Hague%2C%20the%20former%20British%20foreign%20secretary%2C%20and%20Leon%20Brittan%2C%20former%20home%20secretary%2C%20were%20some%20of%20the%20famous%20names%20who%20had%20contested%20and%20won%20from%20this%20constituency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Labour%20Onslaught%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20could%20assume%20it%20will%20be%20an%20easy%20victory%20for%20Sunak%20a%20fourth%20time%20too.%20The%20logic%20goes%20that%20if%20a%20completely%20unknown%20candidate%20in%202015%20was%20trusted%20by%20the%20Richmond%20voters%2C%20why%20would%20they%20turn%20against%20him%20now%20that%20he%20is%20known%20all%20over%20the%20world%20as%20the%20first%20non-White%20British%20Prime%20Minister%20leading%20the%20Conservative%20Party%20to%20the%20July%204%20Parliamentary%20elections%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20face%20of%20it%2C%20he%20is%20safe%20and%20should%20win%20his%20seat%20without%20breaking%20a%20sweat.%20But%20could%20that%20be%20about%20to%20change%3F%20It's%20possible.%20First%2C%20many%20of%20the%20safest%20Tory%20seats%20were%20captured%20by%20the%20Labour%20Party%20when%20it%20swept%20to%20power%20under%20the%20leadership%20of%20a%20young%20and%20charismatic%20Tony%20Blair.%20If%20anything%2C%20the%20Conservatives%20today%20are%20in%20a%20much%20worse%20situation%20as%20all%20predictions%20point%20to%20their%20complete%20decimation%20in%20next%20month's%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Ffancy-teacups-rs-3-8-crore-swimming-pool-5-times-rishi-sunak-came-under-fire-5830370%5C%22%3ERead%20%7C%C2%A05%20Times%20UK%20PM%20Rishi%20Sunak%20Came%20Under%20Fire%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecondly%2C%20Rochdale%2C%20a%20Labour%20stronghold%2C%20elected%20George%20Galloway%20of%20the%20Workers%20Party%20of%20Britain%20in%20a%20by-election%20early%20this%20year.%20Last%20year%2C%20the%20Tories%20had%20already%20lost%20two%20of%20their%20safest%20seats%20to%20Labour%20in%20by-elections.%20These%20results%20were%20shocking%20as%20a%20Labour%20win%20was%20once%20unthinkable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20alarming%20for%20Sunak%20was%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20recent%20local%20elections%20in%20the%20area%20did%20not%20go%20the%20Tory%20way.%20A%20Labour%20candidate%20won%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Frishi-sunak-sadiq-khan-fresh-blow-to-sunak-as-labour-party-win-key-uk-mayoral-polls-against-conservatives-5590664%5C%22%3Emayor's%20election%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20a%20huge%20margin%20in%20a%20mayoral%20area%20whose%20large%20parts%20are%20covered%20by%20Sunak's%20constituency.%20The%20area%20is%20well-established%20as%20a%20Conservative%20citadel%2C%20and%20yet%20Labour%20registered%20a%20handsome%20victory.%20After%20the%20shocking%20result%2C%20Sunak's%20Labour%20rival%20in%20Richmond%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BLabour%20is%20in%20prime%20position%20to%20cause%20a%20real%20upset.%20The%20Conservative%20lead%20over%20Labour%20here%20is%20dwarfed%20by%20voters%20saying%20they%20would%20be%20willing%20to%20vote%20tactically.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETime%20For%20Change%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20boundaries%20of%20many%20of%20the%20650%20House%20of%20Commons%20seats%20have%20recently%20been%20changed%2C%20affecting%20Richmond%2C%20now%20known%20as%20Richmond%20and%20Northallerton.%20Will%20the%20voters%20in%20Northallerton%20be%20as%20welcoming%20to%20Sunak%20as%20the%20voters%20of%20Richmond%20have%20been%3F%20It's%20too%20early%20to%20say.%20But%20a%20recent%20poll%20indicates%20Sunak's%20seat%20is%20at%20risk%2C%20with%20his%20lead%20narrowing%20to%20just%20over%202%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELocal%20newspapers%20have%20carried%20out%20snap%20interviews%20with%20many%20Tory%20voters%20in%20Richmond%20and%20Northallerton.%20Their%20yearning%20for%20change%20may%20not%20be%20good%20news%20for%20Sunak.%20But%20there%20are%20still%20nearly%20four%20weeks%20to%20go.%20In%20politics%2C%20that%20is%20a%20long%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Syed%20Zubair%20Ahmed%20is%20a%20London-based%20senior%20Indian%20journalist%20with%20three%20decades%20of%20experience%20with%20the%20Western%20media)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718088480000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2F99fdua9o_rishi-sunak_625x300_23_April_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Frestless-in-richmond-will-prime-minister-rishi-sunak-lose-the-safest-seat-in-uk-5864795%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Local%20newspapers%20have%20carried%20out%20snap%20interviews%20with%20many%20Tory%20voters%20in%20Richmond%20and%20Northallerton.%20Their%20yearning%20for%20chan